result.name: Pacific Coffee

reviews.text:
Nice place to chill for a while. Big coffee menu. Tea menu is limited. The menu list on the counter is a bit messy and hard to read, also the font is tiny. Clearer signage would help.
I bought a slice of carrot cake which was really stale, but they swapped it for a fresh piece.
Small place near Tin Hau MTR station in Causeway Bay. One poor girl manages to serve all alone. She definitely can do it all. Good coffee, great choice, good food, clean place.
got a seat so relaxing and good for business meeting
This is quite small but the coffee and snacks are great and the staff are friendly..
First time to go to Pacific coffee but did not order coffee! The lemon ice-tea is not bad anyway!
